sunPlatMIB.description: SUN-PLATFORM-MIB.mib Version 1.19 Copyright 2003, by Sun Microsystems, Inc. All rights reserved. Use is subject to license terms. The SUN-PLATFORM-MIB provides extensions to the ENTITY-MIB (RFC2737) where each entity modelled in the system is represented by means of extensions to the entPhysicalTable. Certain of the attributes in the entPhysicalTable are applicable to the model presented by the SUN-PLATFORM-MIB and are explained below: The entries in the entPhysicalTable have the following significance with respect to the SUN-PLATFORM-MIB model: entPhysicalIndex containment, M.3100, fig. 2, index for table extensions. entPhysicalContainedIn containment, M.3100, fig. 2 entPhysicalClass Used to select applicable table extensions, Managed Object Class, M.3100, Table 1 entPhysicalHardwareRev version, M.3100, sec. 5.71 entPhysicalFirmwareRev version, M.3100, sec. 5.71 entPhysicalSoftwareRev version, M.3100, sec. 5.71 entPhysicalMfgName vendorName, M.3100, sec. 5.70 entPhysicalAlias userLabel, M.3100, sec. 5.69 Part of this MIB module is an SNMP version of the Generic Network Information Model (NIM) presented in ITU-T M.3100. This information is further extended by attributes derived from the CIM v2.5 Schema. The containment hierarchy is modelled using the ENTITY-MIB (RFC2737) where each entity modelled in the system is represented by means of extensions to the entPhysicalTable. Where an entity is an instance of a managed object class which is sub-classed from another, the attributes of each class are modelled in a separate table extension. For example for an entity with an entPhysicalClass of module(9), which corresponds to a Circuit Pack, sub-classed from Equipment, an entry will exist in the sunPlatEquipmentTable, with additional attributes in the sunPlatCircuitPackTable. References are made to the following recommendations/revisions: ITU-T M.3100 (07/95) CCITT X.721 (1992 E) CCITT X.731 (1992 E) (01/92) CCITT X.733 (1992 E) CCITT X.734 (1992 E) CCITT X.735 (1992 E) (09/92) CIM Schema: Version 2.5

SunPlatLogAdministrativeState.name: SunPlatLogAdministrativeState
SunPlatLogAdministrativeState.description: An enumerated value which describes the Administrative State of the log as defined in X.735, sec. 8.1.1.1.3.

SunPlatAdministrativeState.name: SunPlatAdministrativeState
SunPlatAdministrativeState.description: An enumerated value which describes the Administrative State of the managed object as defined in X.731, sec. 8.1.1.3.

SunPlatOperationalState.name: SunPlatOperationalState
SunPlatOperationalState.description: An enumerated value which describes the Operational State of the managed object as defined in X.731, sec. 8.1.1.1.

SunPlatAlarmPerceivedSeverity.name: SunPlatAlarmPerceivedSeverity
SunPlatAlarmPerceivedSeverity.description: The value of this object identifies the Perceived Severity of an alarm in the log, including 'cleared' as defined in X.733, sec. 8.1.2.3.

SunPlatAlarmStatus.name: SunPlatAlarmStatus
SunPlatAlarmStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the Alarm Status of the managed object as defined in M.3100, sec. 5.8.

SunPlatEquipmentHolderType.name: SunPlatEquipmentHolderType
SunPlatEquipmentHolderType.description: The Equipment Holder Type as defined in M.3100, sec. 5.26.

SunPlatEquipmentHolderStatus.name: SunPlatEquipmentHolderStatus
SunPlatEquipmentHolderStatus.description: This attribute identifies whether or not a Circuit Pack is present in the slot and if so, is it recognised/acceptable as defined as Holder Status in M.3100, sec. 5.32.

SunPlatEquipmentHolderPower.name: SunPlatEquipmentHolderPower
SunPlatEquipmentHolderPower.description: An enumeration of possible power management states.

SunPlatCircuitPackAvailabilityStatus.name: SunPlatCircuitPackAvailabilityStatus
SunPlatCircuitPackAvailabilityStatus.description: An enumeration of possible AvailabilityStatus flags as defined in X.731, sec. 8.1.2.3.

SunPlatProbableCause.name: SunPlatProbableCause
SunPlatProbableCause.description: A Probable Cause which provides additional information associated with and alarm notification as per ITU-T M.3100 sec. 10.2, X.733, sec. 8.1.2.1., and X.736.

SunPlatPhysicalClass.name: SunPlatPhysicalClass
SunPlatPhysicalClass.description: An enumeration of possible physical classes where entPhysicalClass is specified as other(1).

SunPlatSensorClass.name: SunPlatSensorClass
SunPlatSensorClass.description: An enumeration of possible sensor classes where entPhysicalClass is specified as sensor(8).

SunPlatSensorType.name: SunPlatSensorType
SunPlatSensorType.description: An enumeration of possible sensor types where entPhysicalClass is specified as sensor(8).

SunPlatBaseUnits.name: SunPlatBaseUnits
SunPlatBaseUnits.description: Physical values are represented in the units obtained by (sunPlatBaseUnits * 10 raised to the power of sunPlatExponent). For example, if sunPlatBaseUnits is volts(6) and sunPlatExponent is -6, then the units of the values returned are microVolts.

SunPlatRateUnits.name: SunPlatRateUnits
SunPlatRateUnits.description: If sunPlatRateUnits is set to a value other than none(1), then the units specified by sunPlatBaseUnits are further qualified as rate units. For example, if sunPlatBaseUnits is set to degC(3), and sunPlatRateUnits is set to perSecond(4), then the value represented has the units degC/Second.

SunPlatNumericSensorEnabledThresholds.name: SunPlatNumericSensorEnabledThresholds
SunPlatNumericSensorEnabledThresholds.description: The possible thresholds that may be enabled by a sensor.

SunPlatNumericSensorThresholdResetAction.name: SunPlatNumericSensorThresholdResetAction
SunPlatNumericSensorThresholdResetAction.description: The possible reset actions that may be performed on a sensor.

SunPlatAlarmType.name: SunPlatAlarmType
SunPlatAlarmType.description: This indicates the type of alarm - i.e. the means by which the alarm condition is communicated.

SunPlatAlarmState.name: SunPlatAlarmState
SunPlatAlarmState.description: This indicates the state of the alarm.

SunPlatAlarmUrgency.name: SunPlatAlarmUrgency
SunPlatAlarmUrgency.description: An enumeration of possible alarm urgencies, as defined for CIM_AlarmDevice.Urgency.

SunPlatWatchdogAction.name: SunPlatWatchdogAction
SunPlatWatchdogAction.description: This indicates the action taken by the watchdog if it is not reset within the period specified by sunPlatWatchdogTimeout.

SunPlatWatchdogMonitoredEntity.name: SunPlatWatchdogMonitoredEntity
SunPlatWatchdogMonitoredEntity.description: An enumeration of possible entities that may be monitored by a watchdog as defined for CIM_Watchdog

SunPlatPowerSupplyClass.name: SunPlatPowerSupplyClass
SunPlatPowerSupplyClass.description: An enumeration of possible classes of power supply.

SunPlatFanClass.name: SunPlatFanClass
SunPlatFanClass.description: An enumeration of possible classes of cooling device that may be represented with an entPhysicalClass of fan(7)

SunPlatBatteryStatus.name: SunPlatBatteryStatus
SunPlatBatteryStatus.description: An enumeration of possible battery statuses as defined for CIM_Battery.BatteryStatus.

SunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemPowerState.name: SunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemPowerState
SunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemPowerState.description: An enumeration of possible power states defined for CIM_UnitaryComputerSystem.

SunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemApplicableSe.name: SunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemApplicableSetting
SunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemApplicableSe.description: This specifies a setting which may be applied to an instance of CIM_UnitaryComputerSystem.

SunPlatLogicalClass.name: SunPlatLogicalClass
SunPlatLogicalClass.description: An enumeration of the possible logical classes.

SunPlatLogicalStatus.name: SunPlatLogicalStatus
SunPlatLogicalStatus.description: An enumeration of possible status values.

SunPlatIndex.name: SunPlatIndex
SunPlatIndex.description: An arbitrary value which uniquely identifies the row.

SunPlatPercentage.name: SunPlatPercentage
SunPlatPercentage.description: Used to express a value, in 100ths of a %.

sunPlatStartTime.name: sunPlatStartTime
sunPlatStartTime.description: The time at which the agent was last started; in other words, the time at which sysUpTime was zero.

sunPlatEquipmentTable.name: sunPlatEquipmentTable
sunPlatEquipmentTable.description: The NIM Equipment table. This table augments the entPhysicalTable to provide the attributes defined for equipment under M.3100, sec. 3.2.2. Additional packages may be supported using further table extensions. The sunPlatEquipmentTable is valid for entPhysicalClass values of chassis(3), backplane(4), container(5), powerSupply(6), fan(7), sensor(8), module(9), and other(1).

sunPlatEquipmentEntry.name: sunPlatEquipmentEntry
sunPlatEquipmentEntry.description: An entry in the NIM Equipment table. Each entry of this table represents a piece of equipment within the network element of the type specified by entPhysicalClass.

sunPlatEquipmentAdministrativeState.name: sunPlatEquipmentAdministrativeState
sunPlatEquipmentAdministrativeState.description: An enumerated value which describes the Administrative State of the managed object as defined in X.731, sec. 8.1.1.3.

sunPlatEquipmentOperationalState.name: sunPlatEquipmentOperationalState
sunPlatEquipmentOperationalState.description: An enumerated value which describes the Operational State of the managed object as defined in X.731, sec. 8.1.1.1.

sunPlatEquipmentAlarmStatus.name: sunPlatEquipmentAlarmStatus
sunPlatEquipmentAlarmStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the Alarm Status of the managed object as defined in M.3100, sec. 5.8.

sunPlatEquipmentUnknownStatus.name: sunPlatEquipmentUnknownStatus
sunPlatEquipmentUnknownStatus.description: This attribute identifies whether or not the state of the entity is known as defined as Unknown Status in X.731, sec. 8.1.2.6.

sunPlatEquipmentLocationName.name: sunPlatEquipmentLocationName
sunPlatEquipmentLocationName.description: The specific or general location of the component as defined as Location Name in M.3100, sec. 5.37.

sunPlatEquipmentHolderTable.name: sunPlatEquipmentHolderTable
sunPlatEquipmentHolderTable.description: The NIM Equipment-Holder table. This table augments the entPhysicalTable to provide the attributes defined for equipmentHolder under M.3100, sec. 3.2.3. It is valid for an entPhysicalClass of container(5).

sunPlatEquipmentHolderEntry.name: sunPlatEquipmentHolderEntry
sunPlatEquipmentHolderEntry.description: An entry in the NIM Equipment-Holder table. Each entry of this table represents a component within the network element that accepts a replaceable Circuit Pack.

sunPlatEquipmentHolderType.name: sunPlatEquipmentHolderType
sunPlatEquipmentHolderType.description: The type of the component as defined in M.3100, sec. 5.26.

sunPlatEquipmentHolderAcceptableTypes.name: sunPlatEquipmentHolderAcceptableTypes
sunPlatEquipmentHolderAcceptableTypes.description: The types of Circuit Pack that can be supported by the slot, separated by newline characters as defined in M.3100, sec. 5.2.

sunPlatEquipmentHolderStatus.name: sunPlatEquipmentHolderStatus
sunPlatEquipmentHolderStatus.description: This attributes identifies whether or not a Circuit Pack is present in the slot as defined in M.3100, sec. 5.32.

sunPlatEquipmentHolderPowered.name: sunPlatEquipmentHolderPowered
sunPlatEquipmentHolderPowered.description: The current power management state of the equipment holder.

sunPlatCircuitPackTable.name: sunPlatCircuitPackTable
sunPlatCircuitPackTable.description: The NIM Circuit-Pack table. This table augments the entPhysicalTable to provide the attributes defined for circuitPack under M.3100, sec. 3.2.1. It is valid for an entPhysicalClass of module(9).

sunPlatCircuitPackEntry.name: sunPlatCircuitPackEntry
sunPlatCircuitPackEntry.description: An entry in the NIM Circuit-Pack table. Each entry of this table represents a piece of equipment within the network element that is inserted into and removed from an Equipment-Holder.

sunPlatCircuitPackType.name: sunPlatCircuitPackType
sunPlatCircuitPackType.description: The type of this circuit pack as defined in M.3100, sec. 5.13.

sunPlatCircuitPackAvailabilityStatus.name: sunPlatCircuitPackAvailabilityStatus
sunPlatCircuitPackAvailabilityStatus.description: The availability status attribute as defined in X.731, sec. 8.1.2.3.

sunPlatCircuitPackReplaceable.name: sunPlatCircuitPackReplaceable
sunPlatCircuitPackReplaceable.description: The CIM_PhysicalPackage.Replaceable property as defined by the CIM_Physical Schema.

sunPlatCircuitPackHotSwappable.name: sunPlatCircuitPackHotSwappable
sunPlatCircuitPackHotSwappable.description: The CIM_PhysicalPackage.HotSwappable property as defined by the CIM_Physical Schema.

sunPlatPhysicalTable.name: sunPlatPhysicalTable
sunPlatPhysicalTable.description: The Sun Platform Physical Class Table extension. This table is used to define the physical class of the entity if it is classified as other(1). The sunPlatPhysicalTable is valid for the entPhysicalClass value of other(1).

sunPlatPhysicalEntry.name: sunPlatPhysicalEntry
sunPlatPhysicalEntry.description: An entry in the Sun Platform Physical Class Table extension. Each entry of this table represents a piece of equipment with an entPhysicalClass of other(1).

sunPlatPhysicalClass.name: sunPlatPhysicalClass
sunPlatPhysicalClass.description: An enumeration of possible physical classes where entPhysicalClass is specified as other(1).

sunPlatSensorTable.name: sunPlatSensorTable
sunPlatSensorTable.description: The Sun Platform Sensor Table extension. This table augments the entPhysicalTable to provide the attributes common to all sensors. The sunPlatSensorTable is valid for the entPhysicalClass value of sensor(8).

sunPlatSensorEntry.name: sunPlatSensorEntry
sunPlatSensorEntry.description: An entry in the Sun Platform Sensor Table extension. Each entry of this table represents a piece of equipment with an entPhysicalClass of sensor(8).

sunPlatSensorClass.name: sunPlatSensorClass
sunPlatSensorClass.description: An enumeration of possible sensor classes where entPhysicalClass is specified as sensor(8).

sunPlatSensorType.name: sunPlatSensorType
sunPlatSensorType.description: An enumeration of possible sensor types where entPhysicalClass is specified as sensor(8).

sunPlatSensorLatency.name: sunPlatSensorLatency
sunPlatSensorLatency.description: Where the sensor is polled this value represents the update interval for this sensor measured in mS. Where the sensor is event driven rather than polled, this value should represent the maximum expected latency in processing that event.

sunPlatBinarySensorTable.name: sunPlatBinarySensorTable
sunPlatBinarySensorTable.description: The Sun Platform BinarySensor Table extension. This table augments the sunPlatSensorTable to provide the attributes specific to binary sensors. The sunPlatBinarySensorTable is valid for the sunPlatSensorClass value of binary(1).

sunPlatBinarySensorEntry.name: sunPlatBinarySensorEntry
sunPlatBinarySensorEntry.description: An entry in the Sun Platform BinarySensor Table extension. Each entry of this table represents a sensor with a sunPlatSensorClass value of binary(1).

sunPlatBinarySensorCurrent.name: sunPlatBinarySensorCurrent
sunPlatBinarySensorCurrent.description: The current state of the sensor.

sunPlatBinarySensorExpected.name: sunPlatBinarySensorExpected
sunPlatBinarySensorExpected.description: The expected state of the sensor. If there is no expected value then no value is returned for this attribute.

sunPlatBinarySensorInterpretTrue.name: sunPlatBinarySensorInterpretTrue
sunPlatBinarySensorInterpretTrue.description: The interpretation to be applied to a sensor reading of true.

sunPlatBinarySensorInterpretFalse.name: sunPlatBinarySensorInterpretFalse
sunPlatBinarySensorInterpretFalse.description: The interpretation to be applied to a sensor reading of false.

sunPlatNumericSensorTable.name: sunPlatNumericSensorTable
sunPlatNumericSensorTable.description: The Sun Platform NumericSensor Table extension. This table augments the sunPlatSensorTable to provide the attributes specific to numeric sensors. The sunPlatNumericSensorTable is valid for the sunPlatSensorClass value of numeric(2).

sunPlatNumericSensorEntry.name: sunPlatNumericSensorEntry
sunPlatNumericSensorEntry.description: An entry in the Sun Platform NumericSensor Table extension. Each entry of this table represents a sensor with a sunPlatSensorClass value of numeric(2).

sunPlatNumericSensorBaseUnits.name: sunPlatNumericSensorBaseUnits
sunPlatNumericSensorBaseUnits.description: The base unit of the values returned by this Sensor, as per CIM_NumericSensor.BaseUnits. Physical values are represented in the units obtained by (sunPlatBaseUnits * 10 raised to the power of sunPlatExponent). For example, if sunPlatBaseUnits is volts(6) and sunPlatExponent is -6, then the units of the values returned are microVolts.

sunPlatNumericSensorExponent.name: sunPlatNumericSensorExponent
sunPlatNumericSensorExponent.description: The exponent to be applied to the units returned by this sensor as for CIM_NumericSensor.UnitModifier.

sunPlatNumericSensorRateUnits.name: sunPlatNumericSensorRateUnits
sunPlatNumericSensorRateUnits.description: If sunPlatRateUnits is set to a value other than none(1), then the units specified by sunPlatBaseUnits are further qualified as rate units. For example, if sunPlatBaseUnits is set to degC(3), and sunPlatRateUnits is set to perSecond(4), then the value represented has the units degC/Second. This is as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.RateUnits

sunPlatNumericSensorCurrent.name: sunPlatNumericSensorCurrent
sunPlatNumericSensorCurrent.description: The current state of the sensor as per CIM_NumericSensor.CurrentReading.

sunPlatNumericSensorNormalMin.name: sunPlatNumericSensorNormalMin
sunPlatNumericSensorNormalMin.description: The lowest expected value from this sensor as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.NormalMin. If there is no minimum value then no value is returned for this attribute.

sunPlatNumericSensorNormalMax.name: sunPlatNumericSensorNormalMax
sunPlatNumericSensorNormalMax.description: The highest expected value from this sensor as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.NormalMax. If there is no maximum value then no value is returned for this attribute.

sunPlatNumericSensorAccuracy.name: sunPlatNumericSensorAccuracy
sunPlatNumericSensorAccuracy.description: The accuracy as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.Accuracy of this sensor expressed as a +/-% value in units of 100ths of a percent.

sunPlatNumericSensorLowerThresholdNonCri.name: sunPlatNumericSensorLowerThresholdNonCritical
sunPlatNumericSensorLowerThresholdNonCri.description: This attribute describes the lower threshold at which a NonCritical condition occurs as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.LowerThresholdNonCritical.

sunPlatNumericSensorUpperThresholdNonCri.name: sunPlatNumericSensorUpperThresholdNonCritical
sunPlatNumericSensorUpperThresholdNonCri.description: This attribute describes the upper threshold at which a NonCritical condition occurs as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.UpperThresholdNonCritical.

sunPlatNumericSensorLowerThresholdCritic.name: sunPlatNumericSensorLowerThresholdCritical
sunPlatNumericSensorLowerThresholdCritic.description: This attribute describes the lower threshold at which a Critical condition occurs as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.LowerThresholdCritical.

sunPlatNumericSensorUpperThresholdCritic.name: sunPlatNumericSensorUpperThresholdCritical
sunPlatNumericSensorUpperThresholdCritic.description: This attribute describes the upper threshold at which a Critical condition occurs as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.UpperThresholdCritical.

sunPlatNumericSensorLowerThresholdFatal.name: sunPlatNumericSensorLowerThresholdFatal
sunPlatNumericSensorLowerThresholdFatal.description: This attribute describes the lower threshold at which a Fatal condition occurs as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.LowerThresholdFatal.

sunPlatNumericSensorUpperThresholdFatal.name: sunPlatNumericSensorUpperThresholdFatal
sunPlatNumericSensorUpperThresholdFatal.description: This attribute describes the upper threshold at which a Fatal condition occurs as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.UpperThresholdFatal.

sunPlatNumericSensorHysteresis.name: sunPlatNumericSensorHysteresis
sunPlatNumericSensorHysteresis.description: This attribute describes the hysteresis around the thresholds as defined by CIM_NumericSensor.Hysteresis.

sunPlatNumericSensorEnabledThresholds.name: sunPlatNumericSensorEnabledThresholds
sunPlatNumericSensorEnabledThresholds.description: This attribute describes the enabled thresholds of this sensor as defined for CIM_NumericSensor.EnabledThresholds.

sunPlatNumericSensorRestoreDefaultThresh.name: sunPlatNumericSensorRestoreDefaultThresholds
sunPlatNumericSensorRestoreDefaultThresh.description: Writing to this attribute resets the sensors thresholds to the default settings.

sunPlatDiscreteSensorTable.name: sunPlatDiscreteSensorTable
sunPlatDiscreteSensorTable.description: The Discrete Sensor Table. This table is valid for rows with an entPhysicalClass of sensor(8) and a sunPlatSensorClass of discrete(3).

sunPlatDiscreteSensorEntry.name: sunPlatDiscreteSensorEntry
sunPlatDiscreteSensorEntry.description: An entry in the Discrete Sensor Table. Each entry in this table represents a discrete sensor with entPhysicalClass of sensor(8) and discrete(3).

sunPlatDiscreteSensorCurrent.name: sunPlatDiscreteSensorCurrent
sunPlatDiscreteSensorCurrent.description: The sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesIndex of a row in the sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesTable which corresponds to the current reading of the sensor.

sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesTable.name: sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesTable
sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesTable.description: The Discrete Sensor States Table. This table describes the available states for a discrete sensor in the Discrete Sensor Table. This table is valid for an entPhysicalClass value of sensor(8) with a sunPlatSensorClass of discrete(3).

sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesEntry.name: sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesEntry
sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesEntry.description: An entry in the Discrete Sensor States Table. Each entry in this table represents a possible sensor state for the corresponding sensor in the Discrete Sensor Table. The current state of the sensor is indicated by the value of sunPlatDiscreteSensorCurrent for the corresponding sunPlatDiscreteSensorTable entry.

sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesIndex.name: sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesIndex
sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesIndex.description: A number identifying this sensor state.

sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesInterpretatio.name: sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesInterpretation
sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesInterpretatio.description: This attribute describes the state represented by the corresponding row of this table.

sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesAcceptable.name: sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesAcceptable
sunPlatDiscreteSensorStatesAcceptable.description: This attribute describes whether this value is acceptable as defined for CIM_DiscreteSensor.AcceptableValues.

sunPlatFanTable.name: sunPlatFanTable
sunPlatFanTable.description: The Sun Platform Fan Table extension. This table augments the entPhysicalTable to provide the attributes common to all fans and cooling devices. The sunPlatFanTable is valid for the entPhysicalClass value of fan(7).

sunPlatFanEntry.name: sunPlatFanEntry
sunPlatFanEntry.description: An entry in the Sun Platform Fan Table extension. Each entry of this table represents a piece of equipment with an entPhysicalClass of fan(7).

sunPlatFanClass.name: sunPlatFanClass
sunPlatFanClass.description: This attribute describes the class of the cooling device.

sunPlatAlarmTable.name: sunPlatAlarmTable
sunPlatAlarmTable.description: The Sun Platform Alarm Table extension. This table augments the entPhysicalTable to provide indications of alarm states. The sunPlatAlarmTable is valid for the sunPlatPhysicalClass value of alarm(2).

sunPlatAlarmEntry.name: sunPlatAlarmEntry
sunPlatAlarmEntry.description: An entry in the Sun Platform Alarm Table extension. Each entry of this table represents a piece of equipment with an sunPlatPhysicalClass of alarm(2).

sunPlatAlarmType.name: sunPlatAlarmType
sunPlatAlarmType.description: This indicates the type of alarm - i.e. the means by which the alarm condition is communicated.

sunPlatAlarmState.name: sunPlatAlarmState
sunPlatAlarmState.description: This indicates the state of the alarm as defined for CIM_AlarmDevice.AlarmState.

sunPlatAlarmUrgency.name: sunPlatAlarmUrgency
sunPlatAlarmUrgency.description: This attribute describes the urgency of the alarm as defined for CIM_AlarmDevice.Urgency.

sunPlatWatchdogTable.name: sunPlatWatchdogTable
sunPlatWatchdogTable.description: The Sun Platform Watchdog Table extension. This table augments the entPhysicalTable to provide information about a watchdog timer. The sunPlatWatchdogTable is valid for the sunPlatPhysicalClass value of watchdog(3).

sunPlatWatchdogEntry.name: sunPlatWatchdogEntry
sunPlatWatchdogEntry.description: An entry in the Sun Platform Watchdog Table extension. Each entry of this table represents a piece of equipment with an sunPlatPhysicalClass of watchdog(3).

sunPlatWatchdogTimeout.name: sunPlatWatchdogTimeout
sunPlatWatchdogTimeout.description: This indicates the interval in mS after which the watchdog will timeout if not reset.

sunPlatWatchdogAction.name: sunPlatWatchdogAction
sunPlatWatchdogAction.description: This indicates the action taken by the watchdog if it is not reset within the period specified by sunPlatWatchdogTimeout.

sunPlatWatchdogLastExpired.name: sunPlatWatchdogLastExpired
sunPlatWatchdogLastExpired.description: The time at which the watchdog last expired, as defined by CIM_Watchdog.TimeOfLastExpiration.

sunPlatWatchdogMonitoredEntity.name: sunPlatWatchdogMonitoredEntity
sunPlatWatchdogMonitoredEntity.description: The entity monitored by the watchdog, as defined by CIM_Watchdog.MonitoredEntity

sunPlatPowerSupplyTable.name: sunPlatPowerSupplyTable
sunPlatPowerSupplyTable.description: The Power Supply Table extension. This table is valid for an entPhysicalClass of powerSupply(6).

sunPlatPowerSupplyEntry.name: sunPlatPowerSupplyEntry
sunPlatPowerSupplyEntry.description: An entry in the Power Supply Table extension. Each entry in this table represents a piece of equipment with an entPhysicalClass of powerSupply(6).

sunPlatPowerSupplyClass.name: sunPlatPowerSupplyClass
sunPlatPowerSupplyClass.description: This attribute describes the class of the power supply.

sunPlatBatteryTable.name: sunPlatBatteryTable
sunPlatBatteryTable.description: The Battery Table extension. This table is valid for a sunPlatPowerSupplyClass of battery(3).

sunPlatBatteryEntry.name: sunPlatBatteryEntry
sunPlatBatteryEntry.description: An entry in the Battery Table extension. Each entry in this table represents a piece of equipment with a sunPlatPowerSupplyClass of battery(3).

sunPlatBatteryStatus.name: sunPlatBatteryStatus
sunPlatBatteryStatus.description: The current status of the battery as defined for CIM_Battery.BatteryStatus.

sunPlatLogicalTable.name: sunPlatLogicalTable
sunPlatLogicalTable.description: An extension to the entLogicalTable. This table is used to define the logical class of the entity. The sunPlatLogicalTable is valid for all entries in the entLogicalTable.

sunPlatLogicalEntry.name: sunPlatLogicalEntry
sunPlatLogicalEntry.description: An entry in the sunPlatLogicalTable extension.

sunPlatLogicalClass.name: sunPlatLogicalClass
sunPlatLogicalClass.description: This attribute defines the logical class of the entry in the entLogicalTable.

sunPlatLogicalStatus.name: sunPlatLogicalStatus
sunPlatLogicalStatus.description: This attribute describes the current status of the entry in the entLogicalTable as defined by CIM_ManagedSystemElement.Status

sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemTable.name: sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemTable
sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemTable.description: The Platform Unitary Computer System Table Extension. This table extends the entLogicalTable to provide attributes common to instances of CIM_UnitaryComputerSystem. The sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemTable is valid for those rows of the entLogicalTable with a SunPlatLogicalClass of computerSystem(2).

sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemEntry.name: sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemEntry
sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemEntry.description: An entry in the Sun Platform Unitary Computer System Table extension.

sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemPowerState.name: sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemPowerState
sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemPowerState.description: This attribute displays the computer systems current power state as defined by CIM_UnitaryComputerSystem.PowerState. When this attribute is written to the corresponding power state will be requested from the computer system as provided by the CIM_UnitaryComputerSystem.SetPowerState() method.

sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemApplySetting.name: sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemApplySettings
sunPlatUnitaryComputerSystemApplySetting.description: Setting this will cause the settings corresponding to the value to be applied to the instance of CIM_UnitaryComputerSystem represented by this row.

sunPlatInitialLoadInfoTable.name: sunPlatInitialLoadInfoTable
sunPlatInitialLoadInfoTable.description: The Platform Unitary Computer System Initial Load Info Table extension. This table instruments the CIM_UnitaryComputerSystem.InitialLoadInfo[] property. The sunPlatInitialLoadInfoTable is valid for those rows of the entLogicalTable with a sunPlatLogicalClass of computerSystem(2).

sunPlatInitialLoadInfoEntry.name: sunPlatInitialLoadInfoEntry
sunPlatInitialLoadInfoEntry.description: An entry in the Sun Platform Unitary Computer System Table extension.

sunPlatInitialLoadInfoIndex.name: sunPlatInitialLoadInfoIndex

sunPlatInitialLoadInfoDesiredValue.name: sunPlatInitialLoadInfoDesiredValue

sunPlatLogTable.name: sunPlatLogTable
sunPlatLogTable.description: The NIM log table. It is used to maintain a currentProblemList for each managed object as per M.3100, sec. 5.22. The management system creates entries in this table to specify which types of traps, from which managed object, should be logged. Deleting an entry in this table deletes all entries in the corresponding log. There are separate logs for each notification type/managed object.

sunPlatLogEntry.name: sunPlatLogEntry
sunPlatLogEntry.description: Information about a single trap log as defined in X.735 8.1.1.

sunPlatLogType.name: sunPlatLogType
sunPlatLogType.description: The type of notifications stored in this log. For currentProblemList alarm entries, the sunPlatLogType is set to the sunPlatLogRecordManagedObjectInstance OID value.

sunPlatLogAdministrativeState.name: sunPlatLogAdministrativeState
sunPlatLogAdministrativeState.description: The management system uses this object to stop and start the operations of this object as per X.735, sec. 8.1.1.1.3.

sunPlatLogOperationalState.name: sunPlatLogOperationalState
sunPlatLogOperationalState.description: Indicates whether or not the log is capable of performing its normal operations as per X.735, sec. 8.1.1.1.4.

sunPlatLogFullStatus.name: sunPlatLogFullStatus
sunPlatLogFullStatus.description: If the log is full, this attribute is true.

sunPlatLogCapacityThreshold.name: sunPlatLogCapacityThreshold
sunPlatLogCapacityThreshold.description: Indicates the threshold, expressed in 100ths of a %, at which the log will generate a capacity alarm as per X.735, sec. 8.1.1.3.

sunPlatLogRowStatus.name: sunPlatLogRowStatus
sunPlatLogRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or to delete an existing row in the table.

sunPlatLogRecordTable.name: sunPlatLogRecordTable
sunPlatLogRecordTable.description: The NIM log record table. It is used to maintain a currentProblemList for each managed object as per M.3100, sec. 5.22.

sunPlatLogRecordEntry.name: sunPlatLogRecordEntry
sunPlatLogRecordEntry.description: Information about a single notification associated with a specific managed object. Entries in this table are created automatically but can be deleted by the management system. currentProblemList entries are augmented by the sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalEntry and sunPlatLogRecordAlarmEntry tables. They are automatically deleted when the associated alarm condition is cleared. Entries that represent object creation/deletion alarm log types are augmented by the sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalEntry table. Entries that represent alarm log types are also augmented by the sunPlatLogRecordAlarmEntry table. Entries that represent attribute/state change log types are augmented by the sunPlatLogRecordChangeEntry table.

sunPlatLogRecordId.name: sunPlatLogRecordId
sunPlatLogRecordId.description: A unique number identifying this event as per X.735, sec. 8.1.2.2.1.

sunPlatLogRecordLoggingTime.name: sunPlatLogRecordLoggingTime
sunPlatLogRecordLoggingTime.description: The time at which this trap was logged as per X.735, sec. 8.1.2.2.2.

sunPlatLogRecordManagedObjectInstance.name: sunPlatLogRecordManagedObjectInstance
sunPlatLogRecordManagedObjectInstance.description: The object in the entPhysicalTable or entLogicalTable to which this entry applies as defined in X.721, sec. 10.7.4.13. By convention, this is the name of the first object in the row in the table referenced.

sunPlatLogRecordRowStatus.name: sunPlatLogRecordRowStatus
sunPlatLogRecordRowStatus.description: This object is used to delete an existing row in the table. Note that the only value to which a management system can set this object is destroy(6).

sunPlatLogRecordCorrelatedNotifications.name: sunPlatLogRecordCorrelatedNotifications
sunPlatLogRecordCorrelatedNotifications.description: A comma-separated list of sunPlatLogRecordId values which identify the other events to which this event is correlated, as defined in X.721, sec 10.7.1.11

sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalTable.name: sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalTable
sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalTable.description: The NIM Trap Agent additional information table. This table is used to maintain a currentProblemList for each managed object as per M.3100, sec. 5.22.

sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalEntry.name: sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalEntry
sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalEntry.description: Information text/OID providing further information relating to alarm and object creation/deletion log records.

sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalInfo.name: sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalInfo
sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalInfo.description: An optional OID of an object which provides additional information relevant to this notification as per X.733, sec. 8.1.2.14. This object is only present if it was included in the notification corresponding to this log entry.

sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalText.name: sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalText
sunPlatLogRecordAdditionalText.description: An optional textual description which provides additional information relevant to this notification as per X.733, sec. 8.1.2.13. This object is only present if it was included in the notification corresponding to this log entry.

sunPlatLogRecordAlarmTable.name: sunPlatLogRecordAlarmTable
sunPlatLogRecordAlarmTable.description: The NIM Trap Agent logged alarm trap table. This table is used to maintain a currentProblemList for each managed object as per M.3100, sec. 5.22.

sunPlatLogRecordAlarmEntry.name: sunPlatLogRecordAlarmEntry
sunPlatLogRecordAlarmEntry.description: Information about the alarm-specific attributes of a single trap in the log.

sunPlatLogRecordAlarmPerceivedSeverity.name: sunPlatLogRecordAlarmPerceivedSeverity
sunPlatLogRecordAlarmPerceivedSeverity.description: The perceived severity of the alarm, as specified by the agent that generated it in accordance with X.733, sec. 8.1.2.3.

sunPlatLogRecordAlarmProbableCause.name: sunPlatLogRecordAlarmProbableCause
sunPlatLogRecordAlarmProbableCause.description: An optional probable cause which provides additional information relevant to this notification as per ITU-T M.3100 sec. 10.2.

sunPlatLogRecordAlarmSpecificProblem.name: sunPlatLogRecordAlarmSpecificProblem
sunPlatLogRecordAlarmSpecificProblem.description: An optional textual description which provides additional information concerning the cause of this notification. If more than one specific problem is described in this object, the problem descriptions are separated by CR LF characters. This object is only present if it was included in the alarm trap corresponding to this log entry.

sunPlatLogRecordAlarmRepairAction.name: sunPlatLogRecordAlarmRepairAction
sunPlatLogRecordAlarmRepairAction.description: A list of recommended repair actions separated by CR LF sequences.

sunPlatLogRecordChangeTable.name: sunPlatLogRecordChangeTable
sunPlatLogRecordChangeTable.description: The NIM Trap Agent logged change trap table. This table is used to maintain extra information for log records that represent attribute or state changes as per X.721, sec. 6.2.

sunPlatLogRecordChangeEntry.name: sunPlatLogRecordChangeEntry
sunPlatLogRecordChangeEntry.description: Information about the attribute/state change specific attributes of a single trap in the log. Each of the fields will be present according to the type of the attribute changed. State changes will be indicated using the sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewInteger and sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldInteger objects.

sunPlatLogRecordChangeChangedOID.name: sunPlatLogRecordChangeChangedOID
sunPlatLogRecordChangeChangedOID.description: The changed object's OBJECT IDENTIFIER value in an attribute/state change notification.

sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewInteger.name: sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewInteger
sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewInteger.description: The new INTEGER value in an attribute/state change notification.

sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldInteger.name: sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldInteger
sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldInteger.description: The old INTEGER value in an attribute/state change notification.

sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewString.name: sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewString
sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewString.description: The new OCTET-STRING value in an attribute change notification.

sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldString.name: sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldString
sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldString.description: The old OCTET-STRING value in an attribute change notification.

sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewOID.name: sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewOID
sunPlatLogRecordChangeNewOID.description: The new OBJECT IDENTIFIER value in an attribute change notification.

sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldOID.name: sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldOID
sunPlatLogRecordChangeOldOID.description: The old OBJECT IDENTIFIER value in an attribute change notification.

sunPlatNotificationEventId.name: sunPlatNotificationEventId
sunPlatNotificationEventId.description: A unique ID for this notification.

sunPlatNotificationTime.name: sunPlatNotificationTime
sunPlatNotificationTime.description: The time that this notification was generated.

sunPlatNotificationObject.name: sunPlatNotificationObject
sunPlatNotificationObject.description: The object in the entPhysicalTable or the entLogicalTable to which this notification applies. By convention, this is the name of the first object in the row in the table referenced.

sunPlatNotificationPerceivedSeverity.name: sunPlatNotificationPerceivedSeverity
sunPlatNotificationPerceivedSeverity.description: The perceived severity of the alarm, as specified by the agent that generated it in accordance with X.733, sec. 8.1.2.3.

sunPlatNotificationProbableCause.name: sunPlatNotificationProbableCause
sunPlatNotificationProbableCause.description: An optional probable cause which provides additional information relevant to this notification as per ITU-T M.3100 sec. 10.2.

sunPlatNotificationSpecificProblem.name: sunPlatNotificationSpecificProblem
sunPlatNotificationSpecificProblem.description: An optional textual description which provides additional information concerning the cause of this notification.

sunPlatNotificationRepairAction.name: sunPlatNotificationRepairAction
sunPlatNotificationRepairAction.description: A list of recommended repair actions separated by CR LF sequences.

sunPlatNotificationAdditionalInfo.name: sunPlatNotificationAdditionalInfo
sunPlatNotificationAdditionalInfo.description: An optional OID of an object which provides additional information relevant to this notification.

sunPlatNotificationAdditionalText.name: sunPlatNotificationAdditionalText
sunPlatNotificationAdditionalText.description: An optional textual description which provides additional information relevant to this notification.

sunPlatNotificationChangedOID.name: sunPlatNotificationChangedOID
sunPlatNotificationChangedOID.description: The changed object's OBJECT IDENTIFIER value in an attribute/state change notification.

sunPlatNotificationNewInteger.name: sunPlatNotificationNewInteger
sunPlatNotificationNewInteger.description: The new INTEGER value in an attribute/state change notification.

sunPlatNotificationOldInteger.name: sunPlatNotificationOldInteger
sunPlatNotificationOldInteger.description: The old INTEGER value in an attribute/state change notification.

sunPlatNotificationNewString.name: sunPlatNotificationNewString
sunPlatNotificationNewString.description: The new OCTET-STRING value in an attribute change notification.

sunPlatNotificationOldString.description: The old OCTET-STRING value in an attribute change notification.

sunPlatNotificationOldOID.description: The old OBJECT IDENTIFIER value in an attribute change notification.

sunPlatNotificationCorrelatedNotificatio.description: A list of sunPlatNotificationEventIDs which are correlated to this notification, separated by commas.

sunPlatObjectCreation.description: Indicates that an object, indicated by sunPlatNotificationObject, has been created as defined in X.721, sec. 13.6.

sunPlatObjectDeletion.name: sunPlatObjectDeletion
sunPlatObjectDeletion.description: Indicates that an object, indicated by sunPlatNotificationObject, has been deleted as defined in X.721, sec. 13.7.

sunPlatCommunicationsAlarm.name: sunPlatCommunicationsAlarm
sunPlatCommunicationsAlarm.description: Indicates that a communication alarm has occurred as defined in X.721, sec. 13.2.

sunPlatEnvironmentalAlarm.name: sunPlatEnvironmentalAlarm
sunPlatEnvironmentalAlarm.description: Indicates that an environment alarm has occurred as defined in X.721, sec. 13.3.

sunPlatEquipmentAlarm.name: sunPlatEquipmentAlarm
sunPlatEquipmentAlarm.description: Indicates that an equipment alarm has occurred as defined in X.721, sec. 13.4.

sunPlatProcessingErrorAlarm.name: sunPlatProcessingErrorAlarm

sunPlatStateChange.name: sunPlatStateChange
sunPlatStateChange.description: Indicates that a state change has occurred on the state attribute identified by sunPlatNotificationChangedOID. As states are enumerations of type INTEGER, the old and new states are passed in sunPlatNotificationOldInteger and sunPlatNotificationNewInteger respectively. This is as defined in X.721, sec. 13.14.

sunPlatAttributeChangeInteger.name: sunPlatAttributeChangeInteger
sunPlatAttributeChangeInteger.description: Indicates that attribute identified by sunPlatNotificationChangedOID has changed from the value in sunPlatNotificationOldInteger to the value in sunPlatNotificationNewInteger. This is as defined in X.721, sec. 13.1.

sunPlatAttributeChangeString.name: sunPlatAttributeChangeString

sunPlatAttributeChangeOID.name: sunPlatAttributeChangeOID
sunPlatAttributeChangeOID.description: Indicates that attribute identified by sunPlatNotificationChangedOID has changed from the value in sunPlatNotificationOldOID to the value in sunPlatNotificationNewOID. This is as defined in X.721, sec. 13.1.

sunPlatQualityOfServiceAlarm.name: sunPlatQualityOfServiceAlarm
sunPlatQualityOfServiceAlarm.description: Indicates that a quality of service alarm has occurred as defined in X.721, sec 13.11.

sunPlatIndeterminateAlarm.name: sunPlatIndeterminateAlarm
sunPlatIndeterminateAlarm.description: Indicates that an alarm of an indeterminate type has occurred.
